FBIS3-11587 "drlat056_k_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-056 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Mar 1994 SOUTH AMERICA Argentina Government Denies Approving Patents Law By Decree PY2203191294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 1825 GMT 22 Mar 94 PY2203191294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Buenos Aires, 22 Mar (NA) -- Presidential Secretary General Eduardo Bauza categorically denied this afternoon that the government plans to promulgate by decree the pharmaceutical patents legislation if Congress delays approving the bill now being debated in the Senate. "Under no circumstance will that happen" said Bauza, adding that the government "trusts" the bill will be approved by the Chamber of Deputies "possibly by the middle of this year."
